desc: SBP MotorSynth (Physically Modeled Engine)
author: SBP
version: 1.12.4
changelog: v1.12.4 - ReaPack release prep: refined Electro/Hybrid help and smoothed Turn Influence onset/decay to remove abrupt turn-signal-linked sound appearance. v1.12.3 - Replaced Regen-to-Gearbox routing control with Regen Timbre control, kept regen fully in under-hood Mech bus, and expanded regen timbre shaping from noisy/darker to tonal/brighter behavior. v1.12.2 - Smoothed and reduced Inverter Tone motion to remove siren-like behavior and improved Regen presence/behavior for EV-Hybrid modes.
about:
  Physically-modeled engine sound synthesizer combining pulse-train excitation,
  waveguide exhaust resonance, filtered noise layers, and turbo.
  Features real firing orders and dual RPM control modes.
options:gmem=SBP_MotorSynth_UI

